thread.title: Treat you and your dog to VIB tickets
thread.title_full: Treat you and your dog to VIB tickets

author: Molly Snyder
title: Treat you and your dog to VIB tickets
text:
Earlier this month, OnMilwaukee and Milwaukee Radio Alliance’s B93.3 invited you and your pup to raise the woof at the 2024
Bark & BBQ, Presented by Camp Bow Wow and Bentley's Pet Stuff. The fun takes place Saturday, Oct. 5 from Noon to 4 p.m. on the Harley-Davidson Museum Campus, 400 W. Canal St.
Today, OnMilwaukee is excited to unleash more good news: Beyond Full Spectrum/Tito's VIB (Very Important Barker) tickets are now available for $40.
Each VIB ticket includes:
- Early entry at 11 a.m. to enjoy the event and pooch activities prior to the public.
- 2 drinks for humans (bottomless bowls of water for pups, of course)
- Appetizer buffet on the Motor Restaurant patio
- 1 H-D Museum admission ticket
- 1 Bark & BBQ Beyond Full Spectrum/Tito’s Toss & Chew Toy
- 1 Bark & BBQ bandana
- 1 custom pup cookie and can lid from Bentley’s Pet Stuff
- 1 pup toy from Yelp!
Plus, free samples, vendors, lure course, ball pit, flyball, food trucks and peanut butter licking, costume, best trick, best bark/howl contests on the US Cellular Stage.
Now's the time to upgrade you and your pup's Bark & BBQ experience. Scratch twice if you agree. Or just click
here.
Note: All human VIB's must be at least 21 years of age.
Molly Snyder started writing and publishing her work at the age 10, when her community newspaper printed her poem, "The Unicorn.” Since then, she's expanded beyond the subject of mythical creatures and written in many different mediums but, nearest and dearest to her heart, thousands of articles for OnMilwaukee.
Molly is a regular contributor to FOX6 News and numerous radio stations as well as the co-host of "Dandelions: A Podcast For Women.” She's received five Milwaukee Press Club Awards, served as the Pfister Narrator and is the Wisconsin State Fair’s Celebrity Cream Puff Eating Champion of 2019.
